constraint.name: number of coordinates equals dimension of CRS

constraint.name: no indeterminatePosition
constraint.description: TM_Position.anyOther.indeterminatePosition shall have cardinality 0

constraint.name: valid coordinate
constraint.description:
all coordinate values shall be expressed in the syntax of their corresponding RSID. For temporal coordinates, the value shall be a TM_Position with an appropriate rsid specifying a temporal coordinate reference system.
Note: coordinate values can be decimal degrees, degree / minute / second, timestamps as per ISO 8601, or any other value set the Coordinate Reference system establishes.

properties.documentation: different interpolations yield different values at direct positions -> different coverages. This is conceptual (also for simplified treatment), in practice several interpolation methods might be allowed in a coverage.

constraint.name: values match rangetpye
constraint.description: for all positions: type of position.value = rangeType and for all partitions: partition.rangeType = rangeType

constraint.name: all partitions compatible
constraint.description: all partition sub-coverages shall conform to the super-coverage settings in nativeCrs, rangeType and allowedInterpolation and the coverage envelope shall be a superset of the union of all partition sub-coverage envelopes

constraint.name: domainSet and rangeSet correspond in size
constraint.description: | domainSet | = | rangeSet |

constraint.name: domainSt and rangeSet obey same order
constraint.description: domainSet.element and rangeSet.element must be in same sequence (order)

constraint.name: coverageFunction consistent with Coverage
constraint.description: the domain set of coverageFunction shall be a subset of envelope and the domain of coverageFunction shall be defined by nativeCrs and the range of coverageFunction shall be rangeType

constraint.name: Points on grid
constraint.description: for all elements: geometry() is a Point defined by the grid

constraint.name: At least one axis
constraint.description: | axis | + | displacementAxisNest | + | akgorithmicAxis | > 0

constraint.name: all axes Cartesian
constraint.description:
domainSet CRS is an ImageCRS
which is equivalent to:
for all grid.axis: type is CV_IndexAxis and there is no grid.displacementAxisNest and there is no grid.algorithmicAxis

constraint.name: all axes regular
constraint.description:
domainSet is a RectifiedGrid
which is equivalent to:
for all grid.axis: type is CV_RegularAxis and there is no grid.displacementAxisNest and there is no grid.algorithmicAxis

constraint.name: at least one irregular axis
constraint.description:
domainSet is a ReferenceableGrid
which is equivalent to:
at least one grid.axis is of type CV_IrregularAxis and there is no grid.displacementAxisNest and there is no grid.algorithmicAxis

constraint.name: 2+ dimensions
constraint.description: coverage dimension shall be 2 or more

constraint.name: Grid is index, regular or irregular
constraint.description: for all axis a in domainSet.axis: type(a) is one of CV_IndexAxis, CV_RegularAxis, CV_IrregularAxis

constraint.name: coverage is 2D
constraint.description: dimension of coverage is 2

constraint.name: evaluation as hexagons
constraint.description: for all DirectPosition p: evaluate(p) considers the regular hexagon having p as center.

constraint.name: grid is regular
constraint.description: for all axes: type of grid axis is CV_Index, CV_Regular

constraint.name: geometry is Curve
constraint.description: for all element: geometry() returns a Curve

constraint.name: curve() snaps to nearest curve
constraint.description: The operation curve() shall return the CV_ValueCurve nearest to that direct position. The operation shall return an error message if the direct position is not close (i.e., within the distance specified by the tolerance parameter) to one of the CV_ValueCurves in the CV_SegmentedCurveCoverage.

constraint.name: geometry is surface
constraint.description: for all element: geometry() returns Surface

constraint.name: coverage geometry resembles TIN
constraint.description: for all surfaces s returned by geometry(): s is a triangle, i.e.: bounded by 3 curves connected by 3 points where each of these edges is a straight line

constraint.name: surfaces constitute a Thiessen polygon
constraint.description: the set of all surfaces comprising the coverage constitute a Thiessen polygon.

constraint.name: geometry is Soliid
constraint.description: for all element: geometry() returns a Solid

properties.documentation:
A subtype of a feature. From the abstract specification, a Coverage is a two or more dimensional metaphor for features found on or near a portion of the Earth's Surface. Some examples of a Coverage would be a satellite image of a portion of the earth, a census tract for the city of New York and a DEM for a USGS 1x1 degree map sheet (Topic 6, OGC Abstract Specification, 1998)
A coverage is a subtype of a feature that has pairs of distinguished properties consisting of a geometry property and a function that is defined over the coordinate set that is defined (delineated) by the geometry (Herring, J. OGC Change Proposal 95-039r2)
